    watchOut:['Solving every problem personally — it feels like helping but signals distrust and blocks your team\'s growth.','Measuring your own success by how busy you are rather than how much your team delivers independently.','Holding onto technical tasks because they feel safer and more controllable than the messier work of developing people.'],
