    leaderInAction:'A manager uses the colour model before a difficult stakeholder meeting. She knows the CFO is strongly Blue — data-led, prone to withdrawing under pressure, sceptical of enthusiasm without evidence. Instead of her usual high-energy pitch, she prepares a structured brief: evidence first, conclusion second, three clear risks appended. She leaves silence after each key point rather than filling it. The meeting that previously stalled in scepticism ends with a funding decision inside 40 minutes.',
    watchOut:['Treating colour as a label rather than a lens — "she\'s just a Green" stops your curiosity at the moment it should start.','Believing you\'ve correctly diagnosed someone from a single interaction, especially under pressure — stress masks default style.','Ignoring the cultural baseline — an individual\'s colour sits on top of cultural norms, not independent of them.'],
